The  World  Health  Organization  (WHO)  says  two  premature  babies  died  before  they  could  be  evacuated  with  from  Gaza's  Al-Shifa  hospital  along  with  a  group  of  others  on  Sunday  -  because  of  the  "lack  of  care  available  to  them"  Gaza's  Hamas-run  government  says  that  more  than  14,000  people  have  been  killed  in  the  territory  since  Israel  began  its  offensive  -  including  more  than  5,800  children.
Hamas  killed  more  than  1,200  people  in  Israel  on  7  October,  with  about  240  people  thought  to  have  been  taken  hostage.
